{{Infobox person | name = Daniela Mack | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name above --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1982|4|6}} | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | residence = | nationality = Argentine | citizenship = [[Argentina]], [[United States]] | education = | alma_mater = [[Louisiana State University]] | occupation = [[Mezzo-soprano]] | years_active = | era = | employer = | known_for = | website = {{URL|http://www.danielamack.com/}} }}
'''Daniela Mack''' (born April 6, 1982) is an [[Argentina|Argentine]] mezzo-soprano.<ref>{{cite news | last =Anne | first =Midgette | title =How do you get an audience excited for opera? It’s the vision thing | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''washingtonpost.com''| date =22 September 2017| url =https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/music/how-do-you-get-an-audience-excited-for-opera-its-the-vision-thing/2017/09/21/f0d2bb62-9e19-11e7-8ed4-a750b67c552b_story.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =Anthony | first =Tommasini | title =5 Operas in 72 Hours: A Philadelphia Festival Is a Test of Survival | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''nytimes.com''| date =20 September 2017| url =https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/20/arts/music/opera-philadelphia-o17.html| accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> She was a finalist in the 2013 [[BBC Cardiff Singer of the World Competition]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =BBC Cardiff Singer of the World final | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''theguardian.com''| date = | url =https://www.theguardian.com/music/2013/jun/24/bbc-cardiff-singer-of-the-world-final-review | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Daniela Mack was born in [[Buenos Aires]] and studied at [[Louisiana State University]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Argentina: Daniela Mack | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''bbc.co.uk''| date = | url =http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/2q4txmMsj8Rcwhsrd7WVcy2/argentina-daniela-mack | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> She trained at the [[Adler Fellowship]] Program, an artist-development program at [[San Francisco Opera]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Opera’s emerging stars | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''sfexaminer.com''| date =18 November 2009 | url =http://www.sfexaminer.com/operas-emerging-stars/ | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
==Career== Daniela Mack made her professional debut as Rosina in ''[[The Barber of Seville]]'' with [[Opera Cleveland]] in 2009 while still an Adler Fellow.<ref>{{cite news | last =Donald | first =Rosenberg | title =Opera Cleveland serves up a trim, zany "Barber" | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''cleveland.com''| date =28 March 2009 | url =http://www.cleveland.com/musicdance/index.ssf/2009/03/barber.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> She also debuted at the [[English National Opera]] as Sesto in ''[[Julius Caesar (play)|Julius Caesar'']] in 2012.<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Julius Caesar, English National Opera, Coliseum, review| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''telegraph.co.uk''| date = | url =https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/opera/9582464/Julius-Caesar-English-National-Opera-Coliseum-review.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
In 2016 Mack created the role of Jacqueline Kennedy in the world premiere of [[David T. Little]]’s opera ''[[JFK (opera)|JFK]]'' with [[Fort Worth Opera]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =JFK Fort Worth Fort Worth Opera| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''operanews.com''| date =23 April 2016 | url =https://www.operanews.com/Opera_News_Magazine/2016/5/Reviews/FORT_WORTH__JFK.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
In 2017 Mack created the title role in the world premiere of [[Kevin Puts]]' opera ''Elizabeth Cree'' with [[Opera Philadelphia]] as a part of their O17 Festival.<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Opera Philadelphia Wraps its Season with CARMEN| newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''broadwayworld.com''| date =27 April 2018 | url =https://www.broadwayworld.com/philadelphia/article/Opera-Philadelphia-Wraps-its-Season-with-CARMEN-20180427 | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =David | first =Fox | title =O Festival Diary—Day I: Elizabeth Cree | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''phillymag.com''| date =14 September 2017 | url =https://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2017/09/14/o-festival-diary-day-elizabeth-cree-perelman-theater/#flDY7SWGZHWJHJU6.99 | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =Alyx | first =Reinhardt| title =Daniela Mack is back at Opera Philadelphia | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''outinjersey.net''| date =18 April 2018 | url =http://outinjersey.net/daniela-mack-is-back-at-opera-philadelphia/ | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =David | first =Fox | title =Six Questions with Daniela Mack, Opera Philadelphia’s Carmen | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''phillymag.com''| date =20 April 2018 | url =https://www.phillymag.com/ticket/2018/04/20/six-questions-daniela-mack-opera-philadelphias-carmen/ | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
Mack has sung at opera houses such as the [[Royal Opera House]],<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =Il barbiere di Siviglia, Royal Opera House, London, review: 'The acting and singing make it pulsatingly real | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''independent.co.uk''| date = | url =https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/classical/reviews/il-barbiere-di-siviglia-royal-opera-house-london-review-the-acting-and-singing-make-it-pulsatingly-a7309731.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> [[Washington National Opera]],<ref>{{cite news | last =Anne | first =Midgette | title =Strong women take the lead in Washington National Opera’s ‘Alcina’ | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''washingtonpost.com''| date =5 November 2017 | url =https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/music/strong-women-remain-adrift-in-alcina-at-wno/2017/11/05/4a95aab6-c24a-11e7-84bc-5e285c7f4512_story.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> and [[Santa Fe Opera]],<ref>{{cite news | last =James M. | first =Keller | title =A magical mystery tour: Santa Fe Opera’s ‘Alcina | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''santafenewmexican.com''| date =30 July 2017 | url =http://www.santafenewmexican.com/pasatiempo/opera/a-magical-mystery-tour-santa-fe-opera-s-alcina/article_d71f5b6b-b17a-5507-ba44-a82b99e44b9e.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> among others. On the concert stage, she has performed with the [[Boston Symphony Orchestra]]<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =The Ticket: Classical music | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''bostonglobe.com''| date = 26 February 2016| url =https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2016/02/25/the-ticket-classical-music/1Ros34xkMvkGZA02UnqHBM/story.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> and the [[Chicago Symphony Orchestra]]<ref>{{cite news | last =John von | first =Rhein | title =Recommended Chicago-area classical concerts | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''chicagotribune.com''| date = 13 May 2016| url =http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/vonrhein/ct-chicago-symphony-dutoit-rachel-barton-pine-ott-0513-20160507-column.html | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref> both under the direction of [[Charles Dutoit]].
==Personal Life== Ms. Mack is married to operatic tenor Alek Shrader.<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title =A Cinderella Story: Daniela Mack and Alek Shrader | newspaper =| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =''wqxr.org''| date = | url =https://www.wqxr.org/story/cinderella-story-daniela-mack-and-alek-shrader-classical-valentines-day/ | accessdate =18 May 2018}}</ref>
