'''Ercole Chaia''' (born around 1850 - deceased 1905) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[spiritualist]] who became particularly well known for working as manager of the medium [[Eusapia Palladino]]. He was responsible for convincing the reputed scientist [[Cesare Lombroso]] to attend Palladino's séances, as well as for organising her [[séance]] tours in several European countries.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Natale|first1=Simone|title=Supernatural Entertainments: Victorian Spiritualism and the Rise of Modern Media Culture|date=2016|publisher=Pennsylvania State University Press|location=University Park, PA|isbn=978-0-271-07104-6|pages=96–98|url=http://www.psupress.org/books/titles/978-0-271-07104-6.html}}</ref>
