{{Infobox university chancellor | name = Kenneth Kamwi Matengu | image = | caption = | order =[[Vice Chancellor]] of the [[University of Namibia]]<ref>[https://economist.com.na/36393/human-resources/matengu-clinches-unams-vice-chancellor-seat/Matengu Kenneth Matengu clinches UNAM’s Vice Chancellor seat] Namibia Economist</ref> | university = | term_start = 01 August 2018 | term_end = | predecessor = [[Lazarus Hangula]] | successor = | order2 = | university2 = | term_start2 = | term_end2 = | predecessor2 = | successor2 = | birth_date = 1978 | birth_place = Katima Mulilo, [[Namibia]] | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = [[University of Namibia]], [[University of Tampere]] [[University of Eastern Finland]] | residence = [[Windhoek]], [[Namibia]] | profession =[[Professor]] | spouse = | children = | signature = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Kenneth Kamwi Matengu''' (born 1978 in [[Katima Mulilo]], [[Namibia]]) is a [[Namibia]]n professor and vice-chancellor of the [[University of Namibia]] since 2018 he replaced retired Prof. [[Lazarus Hangula]] in August 2018. He was Pro-Vice Chancellor for Research, Innovation and Resources Mobilization at the [[University of Namibia]] from 2016 to 2018.<ref>[http://www.unam.edu.na/news/pro-vice-chancellor-research-innovation-and-development-appointed Vicechancellor appointed] University of Namibia</ref><ref>[http://www.we.com.na/news/unam-partners-with-the-best Unam partners with the best] Namibian Sun</ref> On 29 June 2018, Matengu was appointed as the third Vice [[Chancellor]] of the [[University of Namibia]] becoming the youngest person to assume the position.<ref>[https://www.thevillager.com.na/articles/13389/unam-appoints-kenneth-matengu-as-vice-chancellor Unam appoints Kenneth Matengu] The Villager</ref><ref>[https://www.lelamobile.com/content/75622/Matengu-appointed-as-UNAM-s-new-vice-chancellor Matengu Appointed as UNAM's New Vice Chancellor]</ref><ref>[https://www.newera.com.na/2018/06/22/who-are-these-people-a-rundown-on-unam-vc-candidates| Who are these people a rundown on unam vc candidate] New Era Newspaper</ref><ref>[https://www.namibian.com.na/68917/read/Matengu-is-Unams-new-VC Matengu is Unams new VC]</ref><ref>[https://www.namibiansun.com/news/-matengu-gets-unam-top-job2018-06-29 Matengu gets Unam top job - Education] Namibian Sun</ref>
==Education==
Matengu did his [[high school]] at Caprivi Senior Secondary. He holds a Certificate in International Relations from the [[University of Tampere]], Bachelor's degree in Geography and Sociology from the [[University of Namibia]], Doctor of Philosophy, Ph.D (exemia cum laudar) in Innovation Diffusion and Development from the [[University of Eastern Finland]]. He has published 50 peer review articles, books and book chapters, as well as international conference papers.<ref>[http://www.unam.edu.na/news/pro-vice-chancellor-research-innovation-and-development-appointed| University of Namibia Pro-Vice Chancellor-Research, Innovation and Development Appointed]</ref><ref>[https://www.cardiff.ac.uk/news/view/548995-kenneth-matengu-personal-story Kenneth Matengu Personal Story] Cardiff University</ref><ref>[https://www.devdiscourse.com/Article/8368-undp-hosts-inaugural-conference-of-igu-commission-on-african-studies UNDP hosts inaugural conference of IGU Commission on African Studies] Devdiscourse</ref>
