{{Use Canadian English|date=August 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox person | image = | caption = {{deletable image-caption|Sunday, 25 June 2017|F7}} | birthname = Ryan Vernon Doucette | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1983|7|23}} | birth_place = [[Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]] | occupation = actor, mime | yearsactive = 2008–present }}
'''Ryan Doucette''' (born '''Ryan Vernon Doucette'''; 22 July 1983) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[actor]].
He is best known for his roles in the films ''[[Cloudburst (2011 film)|Cloudburst]]'', ''[[The Disappeared (2012 film)|The Disappeared]]'', and ''[[Forgive Me (TV series)|Forgive Me]]''. His work in theatre includes ''Cloudburst'' for which he was nominated for a Robert Merritt Award,<ref>{{cite web|title=Robert Merritt Award Nominations 2011|url=http://www.theatrens.ca/home/wp-content/uploads/Nominations-2011.pdf|website=Theatre Nova Scotia Official Website|publisher=Theatre Nova Scotia|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref> ''[[Whale Riding Weather]]'' for which he was nominated for a second Robert Merritt Award,<ref>{{cite news|title=MacIvor, Stone plays top Merritt nominations|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/945958-macivor-stone-plays-top-merritt-nominations|accessdate=17 October 2017|work=The Chronicle Herald|publisher=The Chronicle Herald|date=11 March 2013}}</ref> and his one-man show ''Pourquois pas?''. He won the Merritt Award for his performance in ''His Greatness''<ref>{{cite news|title=Mary Poppins Top Merritt Awards Victor|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/1276307-mary-poppins-top-merritt-awards-victor|accessdate=17 October 2017|work=The Chronicle Herald|publisher=The Chronicle Herald|date=24 March 2015}}</ref>
==Early life== He was raised in [[Clare, Nova Scotia]], and attended [[Université Sainte-Anne]].
==Career== Doucette began his career touring his solo mime show ''Ryan Doucette: Premiere ronde''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Knox|first=Carston|title=Debuting Doucette|url=http://www.thecoast.ca/halifax/debuting-doucette/Content?oid=1726356|accessdate=24 September 2013|newspaper=The Coast Weekly|date=15 July 2010}}</ref> His English theatre debut was in ''Vimy'' at Eastern Front Theatre in 2008. He met with some acclaim for his performance in the original stage production of [[Thom Fitzgerald]]'s ''Cloudburst'' in his native Nova Scotia, and was subsequently cast in the film version starring opposite Academy Award winners [[Olympia Dukakis]] and [[Brenda Fricker]]. He subsequently starred in ''The Disappeared'' and appeared in [[Ronald F. Maxwell|Ron Maxwell]]'s ''[[Copperhead (2013 film)|Copperhead]]''. He appeared on stage again in ''Whale Riding Weather'' and ''His Greatness'' and had a recurring role on ''Forgive Me''.
