The '''Tockwogh''' were an [[Algonquian peoples|Algonquian]] tribe first discovered by Captain [[John Smith of Jamestown|John Smith]]'s party after being informed about them by the [[Mingo|Massawomekes]] ([[Iroquois]]). The name Tockwogh is a variation of [[Wolfiporia extensa|tuckahoe]], a water plant with bulbous roots used for food. At their first meeting, Smith noticed they wore copper hatchets and beads which were traded with their allies, the [[Susquehannock]], mortal enemies of the Massawomeke. The Indians held a feast for Smith's party. Smith noticed that the Tockwogh [[wigwam]]s were very different from those of other [[Algonquian peoples]]: longer, larger, covered with bark, and shaped like ovals. About 20 made a village and villages were surrounded by fields of corn, squash, beans, tobacco. Before leaving the Tockwoghs, Smith traded blue beads, bells and hatchets for corn, pearls, meat, weapons and hides.

